<HEADLINE> Costelloe Named AP Chief in Paris  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Kevin Costelloe, who has directed the expansion
of Associated Press news and business activities in Southeast Asia
for the past three years, has been named bureau chief in Paris.
</P>
<P>
   The appointment was announced Monday by Louis D. Boccardi, AP
president and CEO. Costelloe succeeds Abner Katzman, who has been
named deputy director of World Services at AP headquarters in New
York.
</P>
<P>
   Costelloe, a native of New York City, and a graduate of Brown
University, joined the AP in 1978 in Washington. In 1982, he
transferred to the New York International Desk and was assigned to
Rome a year later.
</P>
<P>
   Costelloe, 47, was named news editor in Frankfurt in 1985 and
became news editor in Berlin in 1990, before being promoted to
bureau chief in Stockholm four years later. He was appointed chief
of Southeast Asia services in Singapore in 1997.
</P>
