<HEADLINE> AP Financial News at 11:10 a.m. EDT  </HEADLINE>
Tuesday, April 4, 2000
<TEXT>
<P>
   Leading Indicators Fell in February
</P>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- A key gauge of future U.S. economic activity
fell 0.3 percent in February, the biggest monthly drop in more than
four years, suggesting that rising interest rates have begun to
take a toll. The Conference Board's Index of Leading Economic
Indicators dropped to 106 in February after rising a revised 0.2
percent in January to 106.3, the private business-financed research
group said today. The decline, the first in the index since
September, was larger than the 0.1 percent drop that analysts had
expected. And it was the largest since the index fell 0.4 percent
in January 1996, Conference Board economists said.
</P>
<P>
   Dow Up 158, Nasdaq Down 144
</P>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks are mixed today, with technology stocks
falling once again and continuing the dramatic decline of the
Nasdaq. Just before 11 a.m. EST, the Nasdaq was down 144.25 to
4,079.43. The Dow industrials were up 158.22 to 11,380.15.
Advancing issues on the New York Stock Exchange led decliners
1,396-1,070. Microsoft stock is down another 2\ at 88| today after
falling 15] yesterday.
</P>
<P>
   Financial Figures
</P>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Financial figures just before 11 a.m. EDT:
Dow Industrials:        11380.15 + 158.22
NYSE Issues:         Advances 1396  Declines 1070  Unchgd  558
NYSE Volume:         266,235,310
