<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-04 14:06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nortel Selling Plants to Solectron  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Nortel Networks Corp. is taking a step away from
brick and mortar, transferring its manufacturing plants in North
America and Asia to Solectron Corp.
</P>
<P>
   The Brampton, Ontario-based telecommunications company said
Tuesday it will sell its manufacturing plants in Calgary, Research
Triangle Park, N.C.; Monterrey, Mexico; and Istanbul, Turkey, to
Solectron. The 4,200 workers at Nortel's plants will keep their
jobs, both companies said.
</P>
<P>
   Nortel, which expects to make $900 million from the sale, will
sign a four-year, $10 billion supply deal with Solectron.
</P>
<P>
   ''This announcement is part of Solectron's core strategy to
continue to expand our business units, capabilities and presence in
the telecommunications industry,'' said Ko Nishimura, Solectron's
chairman, president and CEO, in a prepared statement.
</P>
<P>
   By acquiring Nortel's printed circuit board, new product
introduction prototyping and telephone set assembly centers,
Solectron gets wider access to modern assembly sites.
</P>
<P>
   Nortel said it will realize an annual savings of $250 million to
$300 million annually.
</P>
<P>
   ''Our efforts over the past year have helped to transform Nortel
Networks into one of the most flexible, agile and responsive
provider of high-performance Internet solutions,'' said Chahram
Bolouri, president, global operations for Nortel Networks, in a
statement.
</P>
<P>
   As part of the agreement, Solectron will be setting up a new
operating unit comprised of the acquired Nortel Networks sites. The
unit will be focused on maintaining continuity of supply and
enhancing competitive performance to Nortel Networks, while the
sites transition to the Solectron business model.
</P>
<P>
   Solectron has also submitted an offer to acquire certain
manufacturing operations of Matra Nortel Communications S.A.S.
Matra Nortel is a joint venture between Nortel Networks and
Aerospatiale Matra.
</P>
<P>
   The Milipitas, Calif.-based Solectron is the world's largest
electronics manufacturing services company and offers outsourcing
services to its customers.
</P>
<P>
   The Toronto-based Nortel Networks is the second-largest
manufacturer of telecom products in North America. The company has
expanded its scope to include long-distance calling, telephony and
multimedia.
</P>
<P>
   ------
</P>
<P>
   On the Net: Nortel Networks: http://www.nortelnetworks.com
</P>
<P>
   Solectron: http://www.solectron.com
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-04-04-00 1406 </TRAILER>
