<HEADLINE> AP Financial News at 3:10 p.m. EDT  </HEADLINE>
Tuesday, April 4, 2000
<TEXT>
<P>
   Nasdaq, Dow Drop 500 Then Recover
</P>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- The Nasdaq composite index plummeted more than
500 points today, but bounced back from its earlier lows as bargain
hunters entered the market looking for cheap deals after a steep
two-day selloff. The weakness in the Nasdaq derailed the Dow Jones
industrials, pulling the blue-chip index down sharply in afternoon
trading. Computer-programmed sell orders sent stocks tumbling once
the Nasdaq plunged below 4,000 for the first time since Feb. 1.
Then programmed buy orders lifted stocks from those lows. Just
before 3 p.m. EDT, the Nasdaq was down 225.31 at 3,998.37. At its
low point, the Nasdaq fell 574.57 to 3,649.11. The Dow Jones
industrial average was down as much as 503 points before recovering
to a loss of 188.94 at 11,032.99.
</P>
