<HEADLINE> Teacher charged with having sex with chat-room teen  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   ROCHESTER, N.Y. (AP) -- A middle school teacher was suspended
with pay after being charged with having sex with a 15-year-old boy
he met in an Internet chat room.
</P>
<P>
   The offense came to light last week when Anthony Chalmers, 26,
took a routine lie detector test as part of his application to
become a Rochester police officer, prosecutors said.
</P>
<P>
   Chalmers, of the Rochester suburb of Greece, pleaded innocent
Friday to third-degree sodomy and was released without bail.
</P>
<P>
   Chalmers was a sixth-grade teacher at Monroe Middle School until
he was suspended after his arrest Thursday. According to court
records, he had sexual encounters with the teen between Feb. 19 and
March 24.
</P>
<P>
   Officials said the teen, who lives in Rochester, was not one of
Chalmers' students.
</P>
<P>
   Lie detector tests are a standard practice as part of a criminal
background check for police officer candidates, Monroe County
District Attorney Howard Relin said in Tuesday's Rochester Democrat
and Chronicle.
</P>
