<HEADLINE> Man killed in logging accident in central New York  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   HASTINGS, N.Y. (AP) -- A 20-year-old man running through a wooded
area was struck and killed Tuesday morning by a falling tree, state
police said.
</P>
<P>
   Terry Warren II, of Central Square, was the victim of a logging
accident in the Oswego County Town of Hastings, troopers said.
</P>
<P>
   A crew from DK Enterprises had just finished cutting the 80-foot
tree, and it struck the man as it crashed to the ground, trooper
Edward Foster said.
</P>
<P>
   State Police Investigator Rick Hathaway said the man apparently
became curious at the sound of chain saws and was on his way to
investigate. Troopers said the logger cutting the tree noticed the
man and verbally warned him to leave the area, but the victim
didn't understand the warning.
</P>
<P>
   Last week, a state prison guard was killed while supervising an
inmate work crew that was clearing some woods in nearby Madison
County.
</P>
</TEXT>
