<HEADLINE> Five children involved in bus accident on the way to privateschool  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   MENDHAM, N.J. (AP) -- Two private school students were slightly
injured Tuesday morning when their minibus overturned on the way to
school.
</P>
<P>
   The five students aboard were headed for The Pingry School in
Martinsville, Somerset County, when the vehicle flipped onto its
side in the road at about 7:30 a.m.
</P>
<P>
   The minibus, owned by the Laidlaw Bus Co., had been privately
contracted by parents to take their children to the school for
grades 7 through 12, said Mark Maben, a Pingry School spokesman.
The school has another campus in Short Hills.
</P>
<P>
   The students were taken to Morristown Memorial Hospital. All
were treated and released, a hospital spokeswoman said.
</P>
<P>
   Two students needed stitches for cuts on their heads. The others
were not hurt, Maben said.
</P>
<P>
   The driver had a small cut on her head, Maben said.
</P>
