<HEADLINE> United States 15, Russia 0  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   BARRIE, Ontario (AP) -- Alana Blahoski scored four goals -- three
in the first period -- and the United States allowed only four shots
on goal in a 15-0 romp Tuesday night over Russia in the
International Ice Hockey Federation women's world championship.
</P>
